cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO 

The paper uses deep learning techniques to learn the state space and probability distributions necessary for active inference, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the brain's process theory, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions using deep learning for perception, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with planning, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
